{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "stock-info-service",
    "description": "# Stock Info Service API\n\nA Spring Boot microservice that retrieves real-time stock market details by **ticker symbol** (e.g., `AAPL`) or **company name** (e.g., `Apple`).\n\n## Environments\n- **Local** → runs on `http://localhost:8080`\n- **Cloud** → set your deployed cloud URL in the Cloud environment\n\n## Usage\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Import both environment files (`local.postman_environment.json` and `cloud.postman_environment.json`)\n3. Select an environment from the top-right dropdown\n4. Run any request!\n\n## API Key\nTo get live data for all tickers, get a free key at https://www.alphavantage.co/support/#api-key\nWith the `demo` key, only `IBM` returns live Alpha Vantage data; all others use the mock engine.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "version": "1.0.0"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "{{baseUrl}}",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Set via environment selection (Local or Cloud)"
    }
  ],
